TITLE: Setting Tenant Info in ASP.NET Core
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set the current tenant information using an HttpContext extension method. It shows creating a new TenantInfo object, setting it, and optionally resetting the service provider scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Finbuckle/Finbuckle.Website/blob/main/content/docs/v9.1.1/ConfigurationAndUsage.md#2025-04-16_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var newTenantInfo = new TenantInfo(...);

if(HttpContext.TrySetTenantInfo(newTenantInfo, resetServiceProvider: true))
{
    // This will be the new tenant.
    var tenant = HttpContext.GetMultiTenantContext().TenantInfo;

    // This will regenerate the options class.
    var optionsProvider = HttpContext.RequestServices.GetService<IOptions<MyScopedOptions>>();
}
```

