TITLE: Accessing Current Tenant in ASP.NET Core with HttpContext Extensions
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to access the current tenant information using the HttpContext extension methods. It demonstrates retrieving tenant properties like Id, Identifier, and Name from the TenantInfo object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Finbuckle/Finbuckle.Website/blob/main/content/docs/v8.1.0/ConfigurationAndUsage.md#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
var tenantInfo = HttpContext.GetMultiTenantContext<TenantInfo>().TenantInfo;

if(tenantInfo != null)
{
  var tenantId = tenantInfo.Id;
  var identifier = tenantInfo.Identifier;
  var name = tenantInfo.Name;
  var something = tenantInfo.Items["something"];
}
```

